Here's a video of pro wrestler Bill Goldberg tossing a caddie into a pond","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Alex Myers"},"image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://golfdigest.sports.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/golfdigest/fullset/2017/01/20/588222e28c01e2ff7040d287_170120-goldberg-th.png.rend.hgtvcom.406.406.suffix/1573304260391.png","height":"406","width":"305"},"datePublished":"2017-01-20T09:55:03.292-05:00","dateModified":"2017-01-20T09:55:03.292-05:00","publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"GolfDigest","url":"https://www.golfdigest.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://discovery.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/discovery/editorial/branding/discovery-logo-amp.png","height":"60","width":"60"}},"creator":{"@type":"Person","name":"Alex Myers"},"articleSection":"The Loop","articleBody":"A video involving pro wrestler Bill Goldberg participating in the pro-am portion of the CareerBuilder Challenge has been making the rounds this week. It's 15 years old and it's obviously staged (What isn't when it comes to pro wrestling?), but it's still awesome. In the video, Goldberg finishes his round when someone (we can't tell if it's a golf fan or a caddie) pretends to start punching him. Goldberg promptly picks the guy up and tosses him into a water hazard at PGA West. Here it is: Look at how far Goldberg launched this dude!
